{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778347111,"nonce":"4rRiqstr8J2JVoTmms+RiLPa0kU=","message":"## 6-cell matrix complete — results + variance/anticipation analysis\n\nBranch: `feature/anti-anticipation-6cell-results` (commit `b5e6e6c`) — auth `0ae6fdc9` pending.\n\n### Variance ratio (SD/mean of peak forward velocity, across 5 replicates)\n\n| Cell | Mean PV (m/s) | SD PV | **VR** | Hold drift (mm) | TTP (steps) |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Control (`gru__jerk`) | 0.577 | 0.074 | **0.129** | 19.8 ± 4.2 | 61.9 |\n| Pre-go motor mask | 0.840 | 0.062 | **0.073** | 5.5 ± 0.5 | 61.6 |\n| Hidden smoothness 1e2 | 1.071 | 0.006 | **0.006** | 35.7 ± 1.5 | 47.4 |\n| Pre-go + smooth (combo) | **1.222** | 0.008 | **0.007** | **4.6 ± 0.3** | 52.6 |\n| Variant A (terminal vel) | 0.598 | 0.084 | 0.141 | 19.1 ± 4.7 | 62.6 |\n| Variant B (historical shape) | 0.619 | 0.118 | 0.190 | 16.0 ± 2.2 | 66.4 |\n\n**All 6 cells pass the \u003c 0.5 threshold on SD/mean.** *But:* the prior 0.76 baseline came from a **pairwise RMSE-ratio** metric in `baseline_jerk_vrnn_matrix/RESULTS.md` (within-cell profile RMSE / nearest-neighbor across-cell RMSE), not SD/mean of peak-velocity scalars. **The two metrics are not directly comparable** — see `notes/variance_analysis.md`. This is the most important caveat. Recompute either matrix on the other metric before declaring a win.\n\n### Anti-anticipation (hold-period forward drift)\n\n- Pre-go motor mask: **5.5 mm** vs control 19.8 mm — 72% reduction ✓\n- Combo: **4.6 mm** — 77% reduction ✓\n- Hidden smoothness 1e2 alone: **35.7 mm** — 80% *increase* (counterproductive on its own)\n- Variant A / Variant B: ~16-19 mm — comparable to control\n\n### Headline cell\n\n`gru__jerk_motor_smooth_combo` dominates the matrix: lowest variance ratio (0.007), lowest hold drift (4.6 mm), highest peak velocity (1.22 m/s). The combo of jerk + pre-go motor mask + hidden smoothness 1e2 effectively pins the network to a single fast attractor with no anticipation.\n\n### Investigation outputs\n\n- `results/part2_5/runpod/anti_anticipation_loss_shape_6cell/notes/variance_analysis.md` — full table + metric caveat.\n- `notes/cell2_spike_investigation.md` — disproves the pre-go-spike hypothesis: the apparent downward spikes in the broken plot were artifacts of summing unweighted TermTree leaves; the true loss curve is monotone.\n- 3 figure dirs under `figures/` (HTML in `_artifacts/`).\n- 6 `run.json` specs under `runs/`.\n\n### Methodological flag (separate concern)\n\nThe training script `scripts/train_minimax.py` does not write a `run.json` to its output dir; the 6 specs in this commit were reconstructed from RUN_PLAN.md flags + ps capture. Should be made automatic in the script — separate issue worth filing.","files":null}]}